commands.name: az network security-partner-provider create
commands.summary: Create an Azure security partner provider.
commands.syntax:
az network security-partner-provider create --name
                                            --resource-group
                                            [--location]
                                            [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                            [--provider {Checkpoint, IBoss, ZScaler}]
                                            [--tags]
                                            [--vhub]
examples: az network security-partner-provider create -n MyProvider -g MyResourceGroup --vhub MyVirtualHub --provider Checkpoint

commands.name: az network security-partner-provider delete
commands.summary: Delete an Azure security partner provider.
commands.syntax:
az network security-partner-provider delete [--ids]
                                            [--name]
                                            [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                            [--resource-group]
                                            [--subscription]
examples: az network security-partner-provider delete -n MyProvider -g MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az network security-partner-provider list
commands.summary: List all Azure security partner providers.

commands.name: az network security-partner-provider show
commands.summary: Show an Azure security partner provider.
examples: az network security-partner-provider show -n MyProvider -g MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az network security-partner-provider update
commands.summary: Update an Azure security partner provider.
commands.syntax:
az network security-partner-provider update [--add]
                                            [--force-string {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                            [--ids]
                                            [--location]
                                            [--name]
                                            [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                            [--provider {Checkpoint, IBoss, ZScaler}]
                                            [--remove]
                                            [--resource-group]
                                            [--set]
                                            [--subscription]
                                            [--tags]
                                            [--vhub]
examples: az network security-partner-provider update -n MyProvider -g MyResourceGroup --tags a=b

commands.name: az network security-partner-provider wait
commands.summary: Place the CLI in a waiting state until a condition is met.
